    <div id="frequently-asked-questions" class="content-section">
      <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
      <p>Find answers to common questions about our prep program.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>What are the age requirements?</strong> Our prep program is designed for children aged 5 to 11 years old.</li>
        <li><strong>What is the teacher-to-student ratio?</strong> We maintain a low ratio of 1:15 to ensure personalized attention and support.</li>
        <li><strong>What extracurricular activities are offered?</strong> We offer a variety of clubs, sports, and creative programs to enrich student life.</li>
        <li><strong>How do you support students with special needs?</strong> We provide individualized support plans and resources to ensure all students thrive.</li>
        <li><strong>What is the admissions process?</strong> Prospective students can apply online, followed by an assessment and interview process.</li>
        <li><strong>Is transportation available?</strong> Yes, we offer a shuttle bus service for students within our designated areas.</li>
      </ul>
